ADA William H. Thorie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Cindy Marie Thompson in Court with Attorney Jeremiah James Harrelson.  Cases called at 9:07 a.m.  Includes 14CF73 & 14CT41.  ADA Thorie informs Court of agreement; Defendant pleading to Count One of 14CF73, moving to dismiss Count Two.  State recommending W/H sentence w/3 years Probation.  Concurrent w/St. Croix Co. sentence of 02/02/15.  Defendant will plead Guilty to Count Two of 14CT41 and State moves to dismiss Count One.  State recommending concurrent jail w/prison ordered in St. Croix Co. sentence.  Atty. Harrelson presents Plea Questionnaire to Court.  Court advises Defendant of charges, possible penalties and rights.  Defendant understands.  Court advises Defendant of felony charge, voting and firearms.  Court questions Defendant.  Defendant pleads Guilty to Count One in 14CF73.  Court finds that Defendant has freely, voluntarily and knowingly waived rights and entered plea.  Court accepts plea and adjudicates Defendant Guilty, dismisses Count Two.  Defendant pleads Guilty to Count Two in 14CT41.  Court finds that Defendant has freely, voluntarily and knowingly waived rights and entered plea.  Court accepts plea and adjudicates Defendant Guilty.  Court dismisses Count One.  Atty. Harrelson stipulates to facts.  ADA Thorie and Atty. Harrelson state postitions.  Defendant makes statement.  Court addresses Defendant and sentences.  One Count One of 14CF73, Sentence withheld, 3 years probation.  Concurrent with ES from St. Croix Co.  Same conditions as St. Croix.  Court orders court costs, DNA sample and surcharge.  On Count Two of 14CT41, Court orders 15 days Jail, concurrent with time serving now.  $1179 fine.  DL revocation of 12 months.  Required to complete assessment and drivers safey plan.  IID ordered one year from date of any licensure.  $50 surcharge for IID.  Court advises of appeal rights.
